Note:
C++ Emitter - Buffered output for C++ code generation.

Delegates all buffer management, character/string emission, and growth to the
shared byte-buffer foundation in emitter_common.runa. The wrappers below give the
C++ backend (hir_to_cpp.runa) a stable named API matching the C backend's
emitter, so both backends share one buffer implementation.

Conventions:
- Dynamic geometric buffer growth (amortised O(1) appends) via emitter_common
- C++ uses 4-space indentation
- get_output returns a fresh NUL-terminated copy owned by the caller
:End Note

Import "../emitter_common.runa" as EmitterCommon

Note: ============================================================================
Note: C++ Emitter Structure
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Typed view of the shared 24-byte emitter header for C++-backend code. Storage is
managed entirely by emitter_common; the fields are declared here only for
type-name clarity at C++ call sites.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Three Integer fields at offsets 0/8/16 - byte-compatible with the emitter_common
raw header layout (buffer, capacity, length).
@End Implementation

Type called "CppEmitter":
    buffer as Integer
    capacity as Integer
    length as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Emitter Creation and Destruction
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Named constructor so C++ call sites use the C++-specific spelling rather than the
shared raw helper directly.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_create which allocates the header and an initial-capacity
buffer. Returns 0 on OOM.
@End Implementation

Process called "create_cpp_emitter" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a C++ emitter
    Return proc emitter_raw_create from EmitterCommon
End Process

@Reasoning:
Paired destructor for create_cpp_emitter; frees buffer and header.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_destroy. Null emitter is a safe no-op returning 1.
@End Implementation

Process called "destroy_cpp_emitter" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Destroy a C++ emitter and free its buffer
    Return proc emitter_raw_destroy from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Buffer Management
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Capacity-reservation hook for callers expecting a large emission, avoiding
intermediate doublings.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_ensure_capacity.
@End Implementation

Process called "cpp_ensure_capacity" takes emitter as Integer, needed as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Reserve buffer capacity
    Return proc emitter_raw_ensure_capacity from EmitterCommon with emitter, needed
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Output Functions
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Single-byte append for C++ punctuation (braces, semicolons, commas).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_emit_byte.
@End Implementation

Process called "cpp_emit_char" takes emitter as Integer, char as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit a single byte
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, char
End Process

@Reasoning:
Append a NUL-terminated string - the most-used helper for keywords, identifiers,
types and operators.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_emit_string which measures length once and bulk copies.
Null/empty strings are no-ops.
@End Implementation

Process called "cpp_emit_string" takes emitter as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit a NUL-terminated string
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, str
End Process

@Reasoning:
Combined "emit string then newline" used at the end of statements and directives.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the string then a single LF (byte 10).
@End Implementation

Process called "cpp_emit_line" takes emitter as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit a string followed by a newline
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, str
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Named newline helper so the line terminator can be retuned globally.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits a single LF (byte 10).
@End Implementation

Process called "cpp_emit_newline" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit a newline byte
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
End Process

@Reasoning:
Single space helper between tokens.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits a single SP (byte 32).
@End Implementation

Process called "cpp_emit_space" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit a single space
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 32
End Process

@Reasoning:
C++ convention is 4 spaces per indentation level. Centralised here so the width
can be changed in one place.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Loops level * 4 times emitting a space byte (32).
@End Implementation

Process called "cpp_emit_indent" takes emitter as Integer, level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit 4 spaces per nesting level
    Let total be level multiplied by 4
    Let count be 0
    While count is less than total:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 32
        Set count to count plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Output Retrieval
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Snapshot the buffer into a heap-allocated NUL-terminated copy. Called once at
end-of-translation; the caller owns the returned pointer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_get_output which allocates length+1 bytes, copies, and
NUL-terminates.
@End Implementation

Process called "cpp_get_output" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return a fresh NUL-terminated copy of the emitted bytes
    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Expose the current write position for section-size computation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_length.
@End Implementation

Process called "cpp_get_length" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return the number of bytes written
    Return proc emitter_raw_length from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process
